IMPORTANT CONTEXT: This is an embedded C library for RISC-V. The two dispatch branches (tiling vs VD4DOTS) call completely different kernel functions. The tiling path is copied from a compile-time sibling `#elif` block — this is the standard pattern in this codebase where each `#elif` block is a self-contained implementation variant. The duplication between compile-time branches is intentional and matches the codebase convention.

